{
  "doc_id": "8227",
  "text": "Before initiating the present trial, we performed a retrospective analysis of our own experience in using the pedicled falciform ligament wrap for patients undergoing PD. The study confirmed the high mortality of erosion hemorrhage (39%) and the feasibility of the technique. However, only 39 patients with the wrap were retrospectively identified, and the difference compared with cases without the wrap was not significant [CITATION_1] . We then continued with a systematic literature review and found that the overall reported rate of erosion hemorrhage after PD and pedicled falciform ligament wrap is low (0. 9%). In comparison, the median rate of erosion hemorrhage in studies which reported outcomes of PDs without the use of a wrap was 4.1 (interquartile range, 3.7-4.7) [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
